{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Ricotta cheese","content":["Place milk into mixing bowl and heat <nobr>10 min\/80°C\/speed 2<\/nobr>.","Add white vinegar and heat <nobr>2 min\/90°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Allow to sit for 1 minute. The milk will separate into curds and whey.","Line simmering basket with a nut milk bag or two layers of muslin cloth and set over a large jug. Gently pour milk mixture into simmering basket and allow to drain for at least 10 minutes or up to 1 hour, ensuring that the simmering basket isn't submerged and the ricotta can drain freely.","Transfer drained ricotta (approx. 250 g, depending on time left to drain) into a bowl and set aside."]},{"title":"Dumplings","content":["Place bread, Parmesan, lemon zest, basil, oregano and salt into mixing bowl and mill <nobr>10 sec\/speed 9<\/nobr>.","Add reserved ricotta and combine <nobr>15 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr>, to form a crumbly mixture.","Grease Varoma tray with oil. Then, using wet hands, squeeze ricotta mixture into walnut-sized balls to form dumplings and place dumplings onto greased Varoma tray. Set Varoma aside."]},{"title":"Napoli sauce","content":["Place onion and garlic into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add oil and sauté <nobr>3 min 30 sec\/120°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add all remaining sauce ingredients and cook <nobr>5 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<\/nobr>.","Place Varoma with dumplings into position, secure lid and cook <nobr>10 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<\/nobr>.","Place dumplings and sauce into shallow bowls, sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese and garnish with extra basil leaves. Serve hot."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Ricotta cheese","content":["1500 g full cream milk","40 g white vinegar"]},{"title":"Dumplings","content":["100 g bread, stale or frozen, cut into pieces","100 g Parmesan cheese, crust removed and cut into pieces (3 cm)","½ lemon, zest only, no white pith","2 sprigs fresh basil, leaves only","2 sprigs fresh oregano, leaves only","1 tsp sea salt","olive oil, for greasing"]},{"title":"Napoli sauce","content":["1 brown onion, cut into halves","2 garlic cloves","30 g olive oil","400 g canned diced tomatoes","300 g tomato passata","1 tbsp Vegetable stock paste (see Tips)","100 g water","1 pinch ground black pepper","Parmesan cheese, grated to serve","fresh basil, leaves only, for garnishing"]}],"id":"r79763","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-GlxqQVEM1yA\/XZWZAEZI5II\/AAAAAAAAeGU\/-jvi0OxGUlYNQFJvjjVQ0SknHTkkkYluwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_Rashc6SpZaqLEnZ5.png","title":"Ricotta dumplings with napoli sauce","publishedAt":"2015-08-07T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"28 g","fat":"29.6 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"49 g","calories":"2419 kJ \/ 576 kcal"},"usefulItems":"large jug, nut milk bag or muslin cloth, bowl, shallow bowls","hintsAndTricks":["Please refer to <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i> for the Vegetable stock paste recipe.","If you don't have a nut milk bag or muslin cloth, you can line your simmering basket using paper towel instead in step 3."],"basicInfo":["medium","20m","55m","4 portions"]}